Hence following formula below;\[ \lceil x \rceil := \min \{ k \in Z |k > x\}\; -\;\\    \min \{k \in Q|q>x\}, \;-\;\\    \qquad\;\,+\,[x].\quad \blacksquare\]Hereafter applying similar methodology onto other term too!\[\lfloor 3\sqrt{5}\rfloor = 5\]Combinationally their sum becomes:-$$f\bigg(\dfrac{\pi}{3}\bigg)+f(\sqrt{45})+f(8^{\tfrac{2}{3}}) = \\6 +\color{#FF4F00}{\bf {5}}\quad\,\,\,+ \quad\quad\color{#C00000}{\bf {8}}=19.$$**Hence Final Answer Is* ****** $$f\Bigg(\frac{\pi}{3}\Bigg)+f\Bigg(\sqrt{45}\Bigg)+f\biggl(8^\frac{2}{3}\biggr)=19.$$
